NAME: AUTOMATIC_EXPENSE_ATTENDEES_MAPPINGS
TEXT_VOD__C:
Veeva automatically maps the following fields for the Entry Attendees:
Call Attendees:
AttendeeType -> Call2_vod__c.Expense_Attendee_Type_vod__c
LastName -> Call2_vod__c.Account_vod__c.LastName
FirstName -> Call2_vod__c.Account_vod__c.FirstName
Title -> Call2_vod__c.Account_vod__c.PersonTitle
SystemOwner -> ?
Company -> Call2_vod__c.Account_vod__c.Parent_Account_vod__c.Name
CrnCode -> User.DefaultCurrencyIsoCode for Multi-Currency orgs, otherwise GetUserInfoResult.orgDefaultCurrencyIsoCode
Call "Other Attendees":
AttendeeType -> Concur_Settings_vod__c.Other_Attendees_Type_vod__c
LastName -> "Other Attendees" Last Name
FirstName -> "Other Attendees" First Name
Title -> "Other Attendees" Designation
SystemOwner -> ?
Company -> Call2_vod__c.Accont_vod__c.Parent_Account_vod__c.Name
CrnCode -> User.DefaultCurrencyIsoCode for Multi-Currency orgs, otherwise GetUserInfoResult.orgDefaultCurrencyIsoCode
Event Attendees:
AttendeeType -> Event_Attendee_vod__c.Expense_Attendee_Type_vod__c
LastName -> Event_Attendee_vod__c.Account_vod__c.LastName
FirstName -> Event_Attendee_vod__c.Account_vod__c.FirstName
Title -> Event_Attendee_vod__c.Account_vod__c.PersonTitle
SystemOwner -> ?
Company -> Event_Attendee_vod__c.Account_vod__c.Parent_Account_vod__c.Name
CrnCode -> User.DefaultCurrencyIsoCode for Multi-Currency orgs, otherwise GetUserInfoResult.orgDefaultCurrencyIsoCode
Any custom mappings entered here will be inserted into a sub-query similar to the following:
SELECT Id, Name, (SELECT Id, <attendee_mapping_sfdc_field> FROM Call2_vod__r) FROM Call2_vod__c
SELECT Id, Name, (SELECT Id, <attendee_mapping_sfdc_field> FROM Event_Attendee_vod__r) FROM Medical_Event_vod__c
Example:
Define mapping: Custom9 -> Account_vod__r.Territory_vod__c
Query becomes: SELECT Id, Name, (SELECT Id, Account_vod__r.Territory_vod__c FROM Call2_vod__r) FROM Call2_vod__c
DESCRIPTION_VOD__C: This message describes the fields that Veeva automatically maps when posting Expense Attendees to Concur.

NAME: AUTOMATIC_EXPENSE_ENTRIES_MAPPINGS
TEXT_VOD__C:
Veeva automatically maps the following fields for the Expense Entries:
Call Reports
CrnCode -> User.DefaultCurrencyIsoCode for Multi-Currency orgs, otherwise GetUserInfoResult.orgDefaultCurrencyIsoCode
ExpKey -> Concur_Settings_vod__c.Expense_Key_vod__c
Description -> Call2_vod__c.Id , Call2_vod__c.Entity_Display_Name_vod__c , Call2_vod__c.Call_Date_vod__c
TransactionDate -> Call2_vod__c.Call_Date_vod__c
TransactionAmount -> Call2_vod__c.Expense_Amount_vod__c
Medical Events:
CrnCode -> User.DefaultCurrencyIsoCode for Multi-Currency orgs, otherwise GetUserInfoResult.orgDefaultCurrencyIsoCode
ExpKey -> Concur_Settings_vod__c.Expense_Key_vod__c
Description -> Medical_Event_vod__c.Id , Medical_Event_vod__c.Name , Medical_Event_vod__c.Start_Date_vod__c , Medical_Event_vod__c.End_Date_vod__c
TransactionDate -> Medical_Event_vod__c.Start_Date_vod__c
TransactionAmount -> Medical_Event_vod__c.Expense_Amount_vod__c
Any custom mappings entered here will be inserted into a query similar to the following:
SELECT Id, <entry_mapping_sfdc_field> FROM Call2_vod__c
SELECT Id, <entry_mapping_sfdc_field> FROM Medical_Event_vod__c
Example:
Define mapping: Custom5 -> Account_vod__r.Territory_vod__c
Query becomes: SELECT Id, Account_vod__r.Territory_vod__c FROM Call2_vod__c
DESCRIPTION_VOD__C: This message describes the fields that Veeva automatically maps when posting Expense Entries to Concur.
